HEADWORD: Laxator
<hw>Lax*a"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>laxare</ets>, <ets>laxatum</ets>, to loosen.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>That which loosens; -- esp., a muscle which by
its contraction loosens some part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laxity</ent>⟦br⟧
